olive oil
1 tin coconut milk
1 packet basmati rice
1 carrot
1 packet Apricot Sauce
½ packet tomato paste
½ lemon
1 bag baby spinach leaves
½ tin sweetcorn
½ Fresh Chilli
1 cup water (for the rice)
2 clove garlic
½ packet Veggie Mince
1 sachet Mild Caribbean Jerk Seasoning
¾ cup water (for the chilli)
¼ tsp salt

In a medium saucepan, bring the coconut milk, water (for the rice) and a pinch of salt to the boil. Add the basmati rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce the heat to low. Cook for 15 minutes, then remove the pan from the heat and keep covered until the rice is tender and the water is absorbed, 10 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

While the rice is cooking, grate the carrot. Finely chop the garlic. Drain the sweetcorn (see ingredients). Finely chop the long green chilli (if using).

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Cook the sweetcorn until lightly charred, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a medium bowl. Return the frying pan to a medium high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the veggie mince, breaking it up with a spoon, until browned, 4-5 minutes. Add the carrot, garlic and mild Caribbean jerk seasoning and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are "popping" out.

Add the apricot sauce, tomato paste (see ingredients), water (for the chilli), salt and long green chilli to the veggie mince. Stir to combine and simmer until heated through, 2 minutes.

TIP: If you prefer a saucier chilli, stir in 1-2 tbs of water just before serving.

While the chilli is simmering, slice the lemon into wedges. Roughly chop the baby spinach leaves. Add the baby spinach, a squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil to the charred corn. Season to taste and toss to combine.

TIP: Seasoning is key in this salad, add more lemon juice, salt or pepper to taste.

Divide the coconut rice and Caribbean veggie mince chilli between bowls. Serve with the charred corn salad and any remaining lemon wedges.